Noda Appoints Yoshio Hachiro to Be New Japan Trade Minister

-- B y   A a r o n   S h e l d r i c k
-- 
2011-09-02T02:05:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/noda-appoints-yoshio-hachiro-to-be-new-japan-trade-minister-1-.html
Japanese Prime Minister  Yoshihiko
Noda  picked Yoshio Hachiro, 63, to be Trade and Industry
Minister as he named his Cabinet after being elected to lead the
ruling Democratic Party of Japan earlier this week.  The ministerial line-up was announced by Chief Cabinet
Secretary Osamu Fujimura today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Sheldrick in Tokyo at 
 asheldrick@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
